  <toxic_to_reproduction hazard_type="health">
    <hazard_name>Toxic to reproduction</hazard_name>
    <hazard_id>7.0</hazard_id>
    <classification>Category 1A</classification>
    <hazard_statement>May damage fertility or the undorn child </hazard_statement>
    <rationale>Congenital malformation was produced in 25 persons of 226 pregnants woman which was taking in Lithium for the purpose of medical treatment. It was classified into category 1A based on the description that Lithium was contraindications for the woman with possible pregnancy (ACGIH (2001)).</rationale>
